{"title":"{{< i18n product_backlog >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n product_backlog >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis Backlog translates the **approved scope and roadmap** into a **prioritized,\nexecutable list of work items**, ensuring that:\n\n- Every backlog item supports ecological value\n- All work is traceable to OKR 2.1 and WBS elements\n- Execution can follow an agile or hybrid delivery model\n- Stage‑Gates and KPIs remain enforceable\n\nThis document complements the **WBS** and is used during **Execution and\nMonitoring**, while remaining governed by PMBOK baselines.\n\n---\n\n## Backlog Principles\n\n1. **Ecology first** — items that protect ecological confidence have highest\n   priority  \n2. No backlog item exists without:\n   - WBS linkage\n   - OKR/KR linkage\n3. Items are sized to be:\n   - Estimable\n   - Testable\n   - Reviewable by SMEs\n4. Backlog refinement does **not** change scope without formal change control\n\n---\n\n## Backlog Structure\n\nEach backlog item includes:\n\n- Backlog ID\n- Title\n- Description\n- Priority\n- WBS Reference\n- OKR / KR Reference\n- Acceptance Criteria\n- Owner\n\n---\n\n## Backlog — Phase 0 & 1 (Strategic Foundation + Ecological MVP)\n\n### Epic E0 — Strategic & Governance Foundation\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-01 | Finalize Strategy & Governance docs | High | 1.1 / 1.2 | OKR 2.1 | PM |\n| BL-02 | Baseline KPIs and measurement methods | High | 1.2 | KR1–KR5 | PO |\n| BL-03 | Approve Stage‑Gate framework | High | 1.2 | OKR 2.1 | Sponsor |\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- Documents approved\n- Governance baselined\n\n---\n\n### Epic E1 — Environmental Data Preparation\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-04 | Ingest AUV images (Field 1) | High | 1.3 | KR3 | Data Eng |\n| BL-05 | Prepare metadata and spatial context | High | 1.3 | KR3 | Data Eng |\n| BL-06 | Define environmental annotation guidelines | High | 1.3 | KR3 | SME Lead |\n| BL-07 | Image quality assessment & filtering | High | 1.3 | KR3 | Data Eng |\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- Data completeness verified\n- Annotation guidelines approved by SMEs\n\n---\n\n### Epic E2 — Annotation & Labeling (HITL)\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-08 | Set up AI‑assisted annotation workflow | High | 1.4 | KR1 | DS Lead |\n| BL-09 | Pilot labeling with SMEs (Field 1) | High | 1.4 | KR3 | SME Lead |\n| BL-10 | Review inter‑annotator consistency | Medium | 1.4 | KR4 | SME Lead |\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- SME sign‑off on labels\n- Documented labeling consistency\n\n---\n\n### Epic E3 — AI Model Development (Ecological MVP)\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-11 | Train baseline binary screening model | High | 1.4 | KR3 | DS Lead |\n| BL-12 | Implement precision‑oriented inference | High | 1.4 | KR3 | DS Lead |\n| BL-13 | Generate explainability artifacts | Medium | 1.4 | KR3 | DS Lead |\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- Model meets minimum ecological thresholds\n- Explainability reviewed by SMEs\n\n---\n\n### Epic E4 — Ecological Validation (Field 1)\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-14 | Validate screening results with SMEs | High | 1.5 | KR3 | SME Lead |\n| BL-15 | Compute KPI‑3 (Data Protection Index) | High | 1.5 | KR3 | PM |\n| BL-16 | Prepare G2 Stage‑Gate package | High | 1.5 | OKR 2.1 | PM |\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- KPI‑3 ≥ threshold\n- G2 decision recorded\n\n---\n\n## 5. Backlog — Phase 2 & 3 (Generalization + Assetization)\n\n### Epic E5 — Generalization (Second Field)\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-17 | Ingest AUV images (Field 2) | Medium | 1.3 | KR4 | Data Eng |\n| BL-18 | Validate model on second field | Medium | 1.5 | KR4 | SME Lead |\n| BL-19 | Analyze cross‑field consistency | Medium | 1.5 | KR4 | DS Lead |\n\n---\n\n### Epic E6 — Digital Asset Consolidation\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-20 | Version datasets and metadata | Medium | 1.6 | KR5 | Data Eng |\n| BL-21 | Version model artifacts | Medium | 1.6 | KR5 | DS Lead |\n| BL-22 | Prepare reuse readiness report | Medium | 1.6 | KR5 | PM |\n\n---\n\n### Epic E7 — Closure & Knowledge Transfer\n\n| ID | Title | Priority | WBS | OKR / KR | Owner |\n|----|---------------------|------|------|------|-------|\n| BL-23 | Final documentation & lessons learned | Low | 1.7 | OKR 2.1 | PM |\n| BL-24 | Final G3/G4 Stage‑Gate review | Low | 1.7 | OKR 2.1 | Sponsor |\n\n---\n\n## Backlog Prioritization Logic\n\nPriority order is determined by:\n\n1. Ecological risk mitigation\n2. Dependency on Stage‑Gates\n3. Contribution to KR3 (ecological protection)\n4. Enablement of reuse (KR4, KR5)\n\n---\n\n## Backlog Governance Rules\n\n- Backlog refinement may:\n  - Reorder items\n  - Split items\n- Backlog refinement may NOT:\n  - Add new scope\n  - Remove ecological safeguards\n  - Bypass Stage‑Gates\n\nAll scope changes require formal change control.\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to Other Artifacts\n\n| Artifact | Relationship |\n|--------|-------------|\n| WBS | Structural backbone |\n| Roadmap | Temporal prioritization |\n| OKRs / KPIs | Value measurement |\n| PMP | Execution governance |\n| Risk Register | Risk‑aware prioritization |\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print"